What you need to know:

 “I am a man of integrity. Many corporates do not trust football officials. But I can say without a shadow of doubt that I can comfortably knock on any door to seek for support to revive the game in Nairobi,” he said.Macharia, who touted a “clean cut corporate image” said he is keen to work with the Nairobi Metropolitan Service and the National Department of Public Works to ensure that all stalled public sports grounds are completed to required standards.